<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="70" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="70">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="70">China, Shanxi (Fig. 9).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="3" pageNumber="70" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="70">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="3" pageNumber="70">
Based on the form of the gonostylus, the new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kieffer, 1903" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Peyerimhoffia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peyerimhoffia alpina" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpina">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="71" start="start">Peyerimhoffia</pageBreakToken>
alpina
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mohrig, W" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="13" pageNumber="80" pagination="424 - 432" title="Zur Kenntnis fluegelreduzierter Dipteren der Bodenstreu IX. Beitrag: Gattungen Corynoptera, Bradysia und Plastosciara (Sciaridae)." volume="201" year="1978">Mohrig 1978</bibRefCitation>
). However, the new species differs in having palp is 1-segmented, the tegmen is strongly curved and greatly sclerotized, and the intercoxal area is simple in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kieffer, 1903" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Peyerimhoffia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peyerimhoffia obesa" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesa">Peyerimhoffia obesa</taxonomicName>
. In contrast, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kieffer, 1903" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Peyerimhoffia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peyerimhoffia alpina" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpina">Peyerimhoffia alpina</taxonomicName>
, the palp is 3-segmented, the tegmen is slightly curved and weakly sclerotized, and the intercoxal area bears a lobe-like projection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="71" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="71">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="71">This species is named after its globally inflated gonostylus (Latin adjective obesus = obese).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
